    "what_description": "Peristylus timorensis is a species of orchid in the family Orchidaceae. It is a terrestrial orchid with a short stem and two leaf-like bracts that resemble a sheath. The plant produces a single stem with a few ovate-lanceolate leaves and a raceme inflorescence that bears two to four white flowers with a yellowish-green labellum and a long, narrow spur. The flowers have a rounded lip and three petals with a greenish-white coloration. The species is endemic to the island of Timor in Southeast Asia.",
